AB  - Two experiments examined visual orienting in response to spatial precues.
      In Experiment 1A participants were informed that targets usually (p =.8)
      appeared on the same side as cues in a particular colour (e.g., red).
      Rapid orienting was observed, with both central and peripherally presented
      cues. In Experiment IB cue displays were spatially symmetric. Participants
