AB  - Attention alters three key properties of population neural activity -
      firing rate, rate variability, and shared variability between neurons. All
      three properties are well explained by a single canonical computation -
      normalization - that acts across hierarchically integrated brain systems.
      Combining data from rodents and nonhuman primates, we argue that cortical
      cholinergic modulation originating from the basal forebrain closely mimics
      the effects of directed attention on these three properties of population
