      behavioral performance. It is a common component of aging-related
      cognitive decline and the behavioral changes associated with
      neurodegenerative and other brain-related disorders such as traumatic
      brain injury and schizophrenia. Behavioral changes within an individual
      can reflect alterations at a systems or a cellular level in the brain, and
      monitoring intra-individual variability can therefore provide a warning of
      underlying pathology. Despite frequent reports of intra-individual
