      analyzing the effects of illness and pharmacological agents on brain
      activation. Many fMRI studies now incorporate effective connectivity
      analyses on data to assess the networks recruited during task performance.
      The assessment of the sample size that is necessary for carrying out such
      calculations would be useful if these techniques are to be confidently
      applied. Here, we present a method of estimating the sample size that is
      required for a study to have sufficient power. Our approach uses Bayesian
      Model Selection to find a best fitting model and then uses a bootstrapping
