      processes control subordinate processes by manipulating their parameters,
      reconfiguring them to respond in accord with the current task set. It
      adopts C. Bundesen's (1990) theory of visual attention (TVA) and R. M.
      Nosofsky and T. J. Palmeri's (1997) exemplar-based random walk (EBRW) as
      the theory of subordinate processes. It assumes that a task set is a set
      of TVA and EBRW parameters sufficient to perform a task and that set
