      restricted to situations requiring multitasking, but the precise
      neuroanatomical and cognitive correlates of this problem have been rarely
      investigated. In this study, 60 people with circumscribed cerebral lesions
      and 60 age- and IQ-matched controls were given a multitasking procedure
      which allowed consideration of the relative contributions of task learning
      and remembering, planning, plan-following and remembering one's actions to
