      function of the relative expected value of, and the distance of
      distractors from, the potential valued targets. SRTs and oculomotor
      captures were better correlated to the relative expected value of actions
      than to reward probability, reward magnitude, or overall motivation.
      Together, our results suggest that the level and spatial distribution of
      competitive dynamic neural fields representing saccadic preparation
