      brain areas accounting for this effect. The dominant sources modulating
      visual perception were localized around the parieto-occipital sulcus. We
      suggest that the parieto-occipital alpha power reflects functional
      inhibition imposed by higher level areas, which serves to modulate the
      gain of the visual stream.
