AB  - To test the hypothesis that deep brain stimulation of the subthalamic
      nucleus (STN) restores the inhibitory output to the striatothalamocortical
      loop in Parkinson's disease, we obtained functional brain images of blood
      flow in 10 STN-stimulated patients with Parkinson's disease. Patients were
      immobile and off antiparkinsonian medication for 12 h. They were scanned
      with and without bilateral STN-stimulation with a 4-h interval between the
      two conditions. The order of DBS stimulation (ON or OFF) was randomized.
