      through a well defined dorsal frontal-parietal and ventral
      temporal-parietal network of brain regions, respectively. Recent evidence
      demonstrates that reward-related stimuli also have high attentional
      priority, independent of their physical salience and goal-relevance. The
      neural mechanisms underlying such value-driven attentional control are
      unknown. Using human functional magnetic resonance imaging, we demonstrate
