      and reaction time. The LBA is simpler than other models of choice response
      time, with independent accumulators that race towards a common response
      threshold. Activity in the accumulators increases in a linear and
      deterministic manner. The simplicity of the model allows complete analytic
      solutions for choices between any number of alternatives. These solutions
