      ganglia reduces trial-to-trial neural variability when the bird engages in
      courtship song. Here, we present evidence for a unique, tonically active,
      excitatory interneuron in the songbird basal ganglia that makes strong
      synaptic connections onto output pallidal neurons, often linked in time
