      (SC) that receive short latency input from visual and auditory primary
      sensory areas. The intralaminar nuclei in turn project to the major input
      nucleus of the basal ganglia, the striatum, providing this nucleus with a
      source of subcortical excitatory input. Together with a converging input
      from the cerebral cortex, and a neuromodulatory dopaminergic input from
      the midbrain, the components previously found necessary for reinforcement
      learning in the basal ganglia are present. With this intralaminar sensory
