      capability of mammalian nervous systems. We investigated the role of
      visual (V1), posterior parietal (PPC), and frontal motor (fMC) cortices
      for sensorimotor mapping in mice during performance of a memory-guided
      visual discrimination task. Large-scale calcium imaging revealed that V1,
