AB  - Decision making has recently emerged as a central theme in
      neurophysiological studies of cognition, and experimental and
      computational work has led to the proposal of a cortical circuit mechanism
      of elemental decision computations. This mechanism depends on slow
      recurrent synaptic excitation balanced by fast feedback inhibition, which
      not only instantiates attractor states for forming categorical choices but
      also long transients for gradually accumulating evidence in favor of or
      against alternative options. Such a circuit endowed with reward-dependent
      synaptic plasticity is able to produce adaptive choice behavior. While
