      it is severely capacity limited. Behavioral research has highlighted three
      major bottlenecks of information processing that can cripple our ability
      to consciously perceive, hold in mind, and act upon the visual world,
      illustrated by the attentional blink (AB), visual short-term memory
      (VSTM), and psychological refractory period (PRP) phenomena, respectively.
