      limit of VSTM storage is primarily localized to the posterior parietal and
      occipital cortex, whereas the AB and PRP are associated with partly
      overlapping fronto-parietal networks. The convergence of these two
      networks in the lateral frontal cortex points to this brain region as a
      putative neural locus of a common processing bottleneck for perception and
