      maximal connectivity in each region to a single central cluster of the
      other regions. The topographical architecture of multisensory attention
      may represent a mechanism for specificity in top-down control of attention
      from dorsolateral prefrontal and lateral orbitofrontal cortex and may
      represent an organizational unit for multisensory representations in the
      brain.
