      actions are key executive functions that enable flexible and goal-directed
      behavior. However, to date it has been unclear whether these two cognitive
      operations tap a common action control resource or reflect two distinct
      processes. In the present study, we used an individual differences
      approach to examine the underlying relationships across seven paradigms
