      trial-and-error. Here, we investigate the factors that determine how
      participants learn new stimulus-response mappings by trial-and-error. Does
      learning in human observers comply with reinforcement learning theories,
      which describe how subjects learn from rewards and punishments? If yes,
      what is the influence of selective attention in the learning process? We
      developed a novel redundant-relevant learning paradigm to examine the
      conjoint influence of attention and reward feedback. We found that
