      dopaminergic neurons. Understanding these advances and how they relate to
      one another requires a deep understanding of the computational models that
      serve as an explanatory framework and guide ongoing experimental inquiry.
      This intertwining of theory and experiment now suggests very clearly that
      the phasic activity of the midbrain dopamine neurons provides a global
