      a feature of the target, as predicted by parallel models. Neurons also
      gave enhanced responses to candidate targets that were selected for
      saccades, or foveation, reflecting a serial component of visual search.
      Thus, serial and parallel mechanisms of response enhancement and neural
      synchrony work together to identify objects in a scene. To find a target
